✅ Method: Send Email with Attachment via Gmail SMTP
Step-by-Step SMTP Gmail Setup Commands

Step 1: Install Required Packages
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postfix mailutils libsasl2-modules -y

Step 2: Create Gmail SMTP Authentication File
sudo nano /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
Add this line (replace with your actual Gmail and app password):
[smtp.gmail.com]:587 your_email@gmail.com:your_app_password
-----------> 🔐 Important: You must use an App Password — not your regular Gmail password.
Generate one from your Google account:
➡️ https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
2-Step Verification should turned on & Generate App password you will get --->(mffq kpbk lfyr bpok)<---- Save this in a secure place <--------

Step 3: Secure and Compile the Password File
sudo postmap /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
sudo chmod 600 /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd.db
sudo chown root:root /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd /etc/postfix/sasl_passwd.db

Step 4: Configure Postfix to Use Gmail SMTP
sudo nano /etc/postfix/main.cf
Add these lines at the end:
relayhost = [smtp.gmail.com]:587
smtp_use_tls = yes
smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes
smtp_sasl_password_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd
smtp_sasl_security_options = noanonymous
smtp_tls_CAfile = /etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt

Step 5: Restart Postfix
sudo systemctl restart postfix

Step 6: Send Email with Attachment
echo "This is the email body" | mail -s "Subject Here" -a /path/to/your/file.txt recipient@example.com
-s = subject
-a = attach file
Replace /path/to/your/file.txt with your actual file
Replace recipient@example.com with the target email
